Fri, 13 May 2005 02:17:39 +0100  Vasco Alexandre da Silva Costa:

	Changed paths:
	   M /derclou/trunk/Makefile
	   A /derclou/trunk/sound/buffer.c
	   A /derclou/trunk/sound/buffer.h
	   M /derclou/trunk/sound/fx.c
	   M /derclou/trunk/sound/fx.h
	   M /derclou/trunk/sound/hsc.c
	   M /derclou/trunk/sound/hsc.h

	Totally revamped and bugfixed sound mixing.

	There are now two working sound channels: Sfx and Music.
	Each sound channel has its own circular buffer.
	Mixing is done with floating point precision.

	Music should be properly sampled now.

	Sound is still sampled wrong, but the sound loader code
	has been totally revamped to be more robust.

